30
00:02:55,480 --> 00:02:57,780
The Tesla transformer.

31
00:02:57,960 --> 00:02:59,720
So, the Tesla transformer.

32
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:09,260
Most often this type of device is made by winding copper wire on some frame.

33
00:03:09,760 --> 00:03:17,040
The best frame I think one can use is cardboard pipes.

34
00:03:17,700 --> 00:03:21,520
Which you can get at various household stores.

35
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:30,760
There, films, strips, and other consumer products are wound on this kind of build.

36
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:35,720
Where after the material is sold, they're simply thrown away.

37
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:41,920
Negotiate — the sellers will set them aside for you, possibly for a small symbolic payment.

38
00:03:42,940 --> 00:03:47,940
So, I won't go into the history of making them, let's move directly to the essence.

39
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,220
Usually people act like this.

40
00:03:52,280 --> 00:03:56,920
We have some wire and we have some frame.

41
00:03:57,440 --> 00:04:02,740
We wind the coil and after this the person thinks the transformer is ready.

42
00:04:03,420 --> 00:04:11,100
And even if you're a seasoned Tesla builder and think you know everything about this product.

43
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:15,320
I hurry to assure you this isn't so.

44
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:22,460
The Tesla transformer you can study for years and every time it'll give you something interesting.

45
00:04:22,780 --> 00:04:30,580
You only need to have some persistence, observation, and a lively mind in terms of setting up experiments.

46
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:35,420
Let's move on to calculations of this wound coil.

47
00:04:35,420 --> 00:04:39,560
Generally I don't wind coils without calculations.

48
00:04:39,700 --> 00:04:45,560
That is, I do the calculation initially, and then wind the coil.

49
00:04:46,080 --> 00:04:48,080
But usually people don't act that way.

50
00:04:49,660 --> 00:04:52,180
We have initial data.

51
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:58,040
This is what we should take with maximum care.

52
00:04:58,040 --> 00:05:03,240
We know the wave speed in vacuum.

53
00:05:03,840 --> 00:05:08,820
Use not the approximate value 300 thousand, but the exact one.

54
00:05:08,880 --> 00:05:10,840
This is critical for our calculations.

55
00:05:12,040 --> 00:05:16,120
We need to determine the winding wire diameter.

56
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:23,220
In this case I wound with wire with diameter, including varnish, of 0.36 mm.

57
00:05:23,540 --> 00:05:25,440
Convert it to centimeters.

58
00:05:25,440 --> 00:05:37,800
If the wire is thin, and generally to get accurate calculations, I recommend using a micrometer to measure its outer diameter.

59
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:45,700
If you don't accurately know the wire diameter on the outside, you should always double-check yourself.

60
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:49,120
You'll need such a tool, I think.

61
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:53,800
Further, what do we move to.

62
00:05:54,260 --> 00:05:56,100
The wire diameter is determined.

63
00:05:56,600 --> 00:06:01,380
Now we need to accurately determine the turn length.

64
00:06:02,940 --> 00:06:09,980
Measure it directly on the frame on which we'll wind the wire.

65
00:06:09,980 --> 00:06:16,300
You can calculate it through the standard formula 2πR.

66
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:28,300
But I prefer in practice to take the wire I'll wind with, pull it tight, put a marker mark on it, and then measure.

67
00:06:29,320 --> 00:06:37,260
You should measure in different places on the frame, because the frame may have an elliptical form.

68
00:06:37,260 --> 00:06:42,520
In this case it's clearly round and I don't worry about that.

69
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:46,020
That is, calculate if you have a difference in length.

70
00:06:46,180 --> 00:06:47,280
This is a critical parameter.

71
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:53,540
I did the length of my turn — it came out to 26.55 cm.

72
00:06:53,780 --> 00:06:56,100
I convert this value to meters.

73
00:06:56,640 --> 00:07:02,260
And now we should accurately determine the winding length on the coil.

74
00:07:03,300 --> 00:07:12,100
The physical winding length is measured after you've already wound the coil.

75
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:16,700
In my case it was 30.3 cm.

76
00:07:17,680 --> 00:07:26,880
We need this initial data so we can then do quality calculations of what we got, or what we'll get in the future.

77
00:07:27,580 --> 00:07:30,660
The second variant is preferred — calculate initially.

78
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:43,460
I want to warn you right away that on the internet there are a large number of online calculators that offer you to calculate Tesla coil and its dimensions.

79
00:07:44,460 --> 00:08:02,280
And the most dangerous thing in these online calculators is that many of them output this data not according to the calculations Tesla himself applied, but specifically according to what gives LC resonance on this coil.

80
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:15,220
Yes, such a coil will be similar to a Tesla transformer, but believe me, to a real Tesla transformer it'll have no relation by these calculations.

81
00:08:15,400 --> 00:08:16,540
A useless sparkler.

82
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:24,280
Our calculations will consist of five simple algebraic expressions.

83
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:30,320
To start, we should determine the turn count on this build.

84
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:36,980
For this I take the winding length on the coil and divide it by the wire diameter.

85
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:47,220
My length was 30.3 cm of winding and divide it by the wire diameter, expressed in centimeters.

86
00:08:47,380 --> 00:08:49,280
I get 841 turns.

87
00:08:50,300 --> 00:08:58,460
Next we determine the number of meters of wire that went into this build.

88
00:08:58,980 --> 00:09:10,700
For this turn count we calculated earlier, multiply it by the length of one turn we measured on the frame of our Tesla coil.

89
00:09:11,560 --> 00:09:12,660
841 turns.

90
00:09:12,940 --> 00:09:22,480
Multiply by the turn length in meters and get a total length of 223.28 meters.

91
00:09:23,780 --> 00:09:28,560
Next we should calculate the most important parameter.

92
00:09:29,300 --> 00:09:37,940
For what wavelength the quantity of wire wound on our Tesla coil will be a quarter.

93
00:09:37,940 --> 00:09:54,200
For this, the calculated wire length in meters we multiply by 4, and we get the wavelength in meters that'll correspond to our wound wire being a quarter wave.

94
00:09:54,200 --> 00:10:10,260
That is, 223.28 meters I multiply by 4, and I calculate that the wavelength necessary for my build, to put it at quarter wave, will be 893.12 meters.

95
00:10:11,520 --> 00:10:24,520
Now as item four I calculate the frequency in Hz that should be applied to my build so it becomes at quarter wave.

96
00:10:25,060 --> 00:10:35,320
For this I take the wave speed in vacuum that was in the initial data and divide by the obtained number of meters of wave.

97
00:10:35,320 --> 00:10:54,560
That is, this accurate value 299,792,458 I divide by my physical meters that I calculated, and I get that number — the frequency will be in Hz.

98
00:10:55,400 --> 00:11:02,600
Hertz are inconvenient for us to set, so we convert this value to kHz.

99
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:12,660
Conversion is done by simply dividing this value by a thousand, since in one kHz we have a thousand Hz.

100
00:11:12,820 --> 00:11:24,880
And we have our frequency, which makes 335.7 kHz for this build.

101
00:11:25,780 --> 00:11:33,560
After we determined the frequency, we don't depart from it anywhere.

102
00:11:33,900 --> 00:11:40,860
Remember it, and I want to mention one more moment that comes up in practice.

103
00:11:41,040 --> 00:11:57,220
We calculated it, but you need to understand that this value in kHz corresponds to the frequency that would be for wire stretched in a long line.

104
00:11:57,860 --> 00:12:12,000
And since our coil is rolled into a spiral resonator, here we'll observe some coefficient of wave shortening for a spiral resonator.

105
00:12:13,140 --> 00:12:18,000
So in practice this frequency will be slightly lower.

106
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:30,440
Here for this build, the calculated is 335.7 kHz, and in practice it turned out to 330 kHz — that is, 5 kHz lower.

107
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:41,220
Now, when we have all the calculations, we can move to testing this build.

108
00:12:41,220 --> 00:13:04,760
For conducting measurements of LC resonance of this coil, we need a signal generator — preferably of sine form — an oscilloscope, one turn of wire that'll play the role of inductor and be located closer to the cold end of the Tesla transformer.

109
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:08,120
And good grounding without fail.

110
00:13:08,240 --> 00:13:11,760
The grounding in this case at me is 25 meters.

111
00:13:12,620 --> 00:13:38,980
Guys, there's such unpleasant statistics that's already manifesting on the example of three of my acquaintances, that people who live in apartments where there's a large amount of rebar in the walls — the coil during wave reduction and LC resonance doesn't show amplitude increase.

112
00:13:40,000 --> 00:13:52,780
And when the same people conduct the experiment going from their apartment to an open area — that is for example to a country house — there it works excellently.

113
00:13:53,600 --> 00:14:03,880
That is, either they have bad grounding because they live on some floor above the first and have no way to make it.

114
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:08,880
Or the rebar in building walls actually affects.

115
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:17,100
And if you have such data, when you do this, please write in the comments because I'm collecting these statistics.

116
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:23,060
That is, it's already starting to be confirmed that the Tesla transformer behaves differently in an apartment.

117
00:14:23,620 --> 00:14:31,230
And from this we can make conclusions on why many can't tune or make the same OU devices.

118
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:35,140
A sad situation, that.

119
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:37,400
Well OK, let's move on.

120
00:14:37,960 --> 00:14:39,180
Good grounding.

121
00:14:39,520 --> 00:14:41,100
I stopped on this moment.

122
00:14:41,420 --> 00:14:47,140
And we know our frequency from the calculations we got.

123
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:52,220
335.7 kHz.

124
00:14:53,180 --> 00:14:57,220
Let me set this frequency now.

125
00:14:58,220 --> 00:14:59,520
Like this.

126
00:15:04,350 --> 00:15:05,870
The device is set.

127
00:15:06,510 --> 00:15:15,430
You can see the probe and oscilloscope are nearby, at some distance from the hot end of the Tesla transformer.

128
00:15:16,130 --> 00:15:20,350
And there's something on the oscilloscope.

129
00:15:20,450 --> 00:15:23,610
These are pickups, mains pickups of 50 Hz.

130
00:15:23,610 --> 00:15:25,530
How are they removed?

131
00:15:26,170 --> 00:15:33,530
We need to ground the common probe of the oscilloscope to the same earth as the Tesla transformer.

132
00:15:34,230 --> 00:15:37,330
I do this with an additional conductor.

133
00:15:38,070 --> 00:15:41,950
And see — the pickups disappeared for us.

134
00:15:42,050 --> 00:15:44,090
Now we can do quality measurements.

135
00:15:44,990 --> 00:15:46,430
Apply the signal.

136
00:15:47,910 --> 00:15:51,410
And here something appeared for us.

137
00:15:51,990 --> 00:15:58,470
But clearly, although we applied our calculated, we don't clearly see a manifestation.

138
00:15:59,570 --> 00:16:05,490
Now we'll move on to the moment where we need to determine LC resonance.

139
00:16:05,490 --> 00:16:13,150
I'll smoothly raise the frequency applied from the signal generator.

140
00:16:13,230 --> 00:16:18,310
And we'll follow the amplitude on the oscilloscope.

141
00:16:19,690 --> 00:16:23,650
So, here we see, a sine wave appeared for us.

142
00:16:25,490 --> 00:16:29,310
And I continue to smoothly raise the frequency.

143
00:16:31,070 --> 00:16:33,190
See the amplitude growth.

144
00:16:34,190 --> 00:16:39,810
I can reduce the volts-per-division setting.

145
00:16:41,870 --> 00:16:44,690
And reach the maximum.

146
00:16:45,370 --> 00:16:49,250
Amplitude grew more — now already 20 volts per division.

147
00:16:51,470 --> 00:16:53,250
And reached the maximum.

148
00:16:54,950 --> 00:16:59,690
The maximum makes — the frequency for us is 490 kHz.

149
00:16:59,690 --> 00:17:04,070
How to check that this is actually LC resonance.

150
00:17:04,610 --> 00:17:11,690
Watch my hand, I bring it to the coil and the amplitude changes for us.

151
00:17:12,670 --> 00:17:16,430
That is, my hand is an isolated capacity.

152
00:17:18,390 --> 00:17:28,150
You see that with our calculated 335.7 kHz, this doesn't correspond in any way.

153
00:17:28,150 --> 00:17:38,410
Although if we bring a neon lamp now, and say touch it to the hot end, the neon will burn at us.

154
00:17:39,110 --> 00:17:41,670
Possibly here it doesn't glow.

155
00:17:42,890 --> 00:17:49,430
Kind of, the Tesla transformer is ready, but it works at LC resonance.

156
00:17:50,510 --> 00:17:57,210
And this frequency, if you enter it into an online calculator, approximately the online calculator will count for you.

157
00:17:58,150 --> 00:18:00,650
You'll stop, well, and nothing good.

158
00:18:01,530 --> 00:18:07,370
And as you see, when I did the calculations, I didn't turn to any online calculator at all.

159
00:18:07,890 --> 00:18:12,090
Everything counted by the simplest algebraic expressions.

160
00:18:14,010 --> 00:18:17,350
So, we now have a delta of difference.

161
00:18:17,890 --> 00:18:19,890
Calculated and actual.

162
00:18:20,030 --> 00:18:21,690
490 kHz.

163
00:18:21,690 --> 00:18:25,310
So, here now a very important moment.

164
00:18:25,730 --> 00:18:29,510
We have a difference, what do we need to do.

165
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:32,150
We know the calculated, and LC is higher.

166
00:18:32,290 --> 00:18:37,650
So we need to lower this LC resonance frequency.

167
00:18:38,070 --> 00:18:40,930
How is LC resonance frequency lowered?

168
00:18:42,850 --> 00:18:47,010
LC resonance for us is resonance of two positions.

169
00:18:48,110 --> 00:18:50,070
Capacitor and coil.

170
00:18:50,230 --> 00:18:52,530
That is inductance and capacity.

171
00:18:52,890 --> 00:18:59,490
The inductance is the turn count at their certain diameter.

172
00:19:00,030 --> 00:19:04,310
And the capacity is the interturn capacity of the wire itself.

173
00:19:04,690 --> 00:19:07,030
Here they form LC resonance for us.

174
00:19:07,730 --> 00:19:13,370
And we have two variants of how we can reduce LC resonance frequency.

175
00:19:13,370 --> 00:19:23,570
This is to apply in practice such ferrite rods from antennas of radio receivers.

176
00:19:24,150 --> 00:19:26,230
Say, increase inductance.

177
00:19:26,670 --> 00:19:28,710
Or add capacity.

178
00:19:29,530 --> 00:19:36,610
In the best case, you should add capacity at the hot end of the Tesla transformer.

179
00:19:36,670 --> 00:19:41,950
What we see at most builds in the form of toroids or spheres.

180
00:19:41,950 --> 00:19:52,310
Here I made this sphere that we'll connect to this build.

181
00:19:53,790 --> 00:20:01,370
Now observe what'll happen with LC resonance when a ferrite rod is introduced into the Tesla coil.

182
00:20:02,090 --> 00:20:03,070
I introduce the rod.

183
00:20:04,290 --> 00:20:07,810
You see it tunes most accurately first.

184
00:20:08,270 --> 00:20:09,770
Observe the amplitude.

185
00:20:10,460 --> 00:20:12,670
And further a drop happens.

186
00:20:13,250 --> 00:20:17,050
Here we introduced the rod to some distance, the amplitude went down.

187
00:20:17,610 --> 00:20:26,210
Now we can go down in frequency and also reach maximum amplitude.

188
00:20:27,210 --> 00:20:30,590
See, the amplitude grows with reducing frequency.

189
00:20:35,450 --> 00:20:47,790
In this case, introducing the ferrite rod at a certain depth lowered the frequency from 490 to 418 kHz.

190
00:20:48,430 --> 00:20:51,690
So the method works and we can use it.

191
00:20:53,010 --> 00:20:58,310
This Tesla transformer is a good transformer.

192
00:20:58,310 --> 00:21:02,490
Here we have a relatively small spread in frequency.

193
00:21:03,050 --> 00:21:06,090
330 and 490 kHz.

194
00:21:07,490 --> 00:21:11,470
It'd be ideal if all parameters here converged.

195
00:21:11,570 --> 00:21:12,990
That is, how do they converge?

196
00:21:13,110 --> 00:21:16,610
We need to make a spread of these two frequencies.

197
00:21:17,160 --> 00:21:17,530
Calculated.

198
00:21:17,870 --> 00:21:20,230
And LC resonance frequency.

199
00:21:20,390 --> 00:21:25,750
Without any tricks in the form of increasing inductance.

200
00:21:25,750 --> 00:21:33,090
When these frequencies are at the minimum distance from each other in the frequency range.

201
00:21:33,190 --> 00:21:35,050
That is, we need a minimum difference.

202
00:21:36,410 --> 00:21:38,590
But this isn't all so bad.

203
00:21:38,750 --> 00:21:45,750
We can adjust all this matter with the help of such simple devices.

204
00:21:46,730 --> 00:21:48,850
Which Tesla himself used.

205
00:21:49,600 --> 00:21:59,690
But you must remember that increasing capacity leads to worsening of the oscillating circuit's quality factor.

206
00:21:59,870 --> 00:22:06,310
That is, attaching this capacity, we slightly worsen parameters of the whole system.

207
00:22:06,830 --> 00:22:10,550
In this case it's not critical because the spread is small.

208
00:22:11,170 --> 00:22:15,090
In practice the diameter of this sphere is a bit small.

209
00:22:15,090 --> 00:22:20,270
It needs to be increased almost twice for this Tesla coil.

210
00:22:20,430 --> 00:22:22,090
And here everything will be optimal.

211
00:22:23,150 --> 00:22:27,130
Now one more moment with LC resonance that may come up in practice.

212
00:22:27,790 --> 00:22:31,830
As we see in this build, I have a difference in frequencies.

213
00:22:31,930 --> 00:22:38,670
At that, my LC resonance frequency is higher than the wave frequency on wire length.

214
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:50,030
In this case everything is easily fixable by introducing ferrite or connecting an additional isolated capacity.

215
00:22:50,950 --> 00:22:57,390
And there are situations when on the contrary, measured, the LC resonance frequency is lower.

216
00:22:57,950 --> 00:23:01,670
This is the worst that can happen.

217
00:23:02,590 --> 00:23:04,950
The build will need to be redone entirely.

218
00:23:04,950 --> 00:23:12,890
Because in such a case you can in no way raise the LC resonance frequency up.

219
00:23:13,410 --> 00:23:18,090
By all the methods shown above it'll only reduce.

220
00:23:19,170 --> 00:23:34,870
In this case only physical unwinding of wire may help, until at you the LC resonance parameters become the same as the parameters of the wave on wire length.

221
00:23:34,950 --> 00:23:36,230
Or slightly above it.

222
00:23:36,610 --> 00:23:41,970
But usually in practice this is an unsuitable coil that should be rewound.

223
00:23:42,650 --> 00:23:53,770
Applying — if at you LC resonance even without connected isolated capacity is below in frequency, you need to usually reduce the frame diameter.

224
00:23:53,850 --> 00:24:00,310
Because reducing frame diameter, we reduce the total inductance of the coil.

225
00:24:02,070 --> 00:24:03,610
But back to the experiment.

226
00:24:04,950 --> 00:24:07,390
I connected the isolated capacity.

227
00:24:09,190 --> 00:24:16,050
It can connect directly, so it'd be near the Tesla transformer.

228
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:20,230
For this I have one more soldering place for connection.

229
00:24:20,350 --> 00:24:24,610
In this case I used it for another experiment slightly, but it won't hurt us.

230
00:24:25,610 --> 00:24:30,950
So, now we'll lower the frequency.

231
00:24:31,710 --> 00:24:37,870
And find at what frequency now LC resonance will be at us, with the sphere connected.

232
00:24:39,810 --> 00:24:41,790
Going down.

233
00:24:45,110 --> 00:24:53,750
And the frequency here at us is somewhere, maximum corresponds, 380 kHz.

234
00:24:54,610 --> 00:25:05,310
That is, understand that connecting such a sphere, the frequency from 490 kHz dropped to 380.

235
00:25:05,830 --> 00:25:10,390
But again it doesn't reach my calculated.

236
00:25:11,130 --> 00:25:17,890
Turns out this sphere isn't quite suitable for quality work of the Tesla transformer.

237
00:25:18,170 --> 00:25:23,930
And its diameter should be increased in practice until LC resonance falls.

238
00:25:24,610 --> 00:25:36,090
But since I don't have another sphere, I'll additionally introduce a ferrite rod, thereby increasing inductance and lowering LC resonance frequency.

239
00:25:36,370 --> 00:25:41,750
Now I set the frequency on the lab signal generator to 330 kHz.

240
00:25:42,390 --> 00:25:58,570
And now we'll observe how when introducing the ferrite rod into the coil, we'll observe the combination of the wave from LC resonance with the wave on wire length.

241
00:25:59,790 --> 00:26:10,890
I introduce the core into the coil and see that amplitude for us starts growing from maximum amplitude.

242
00:26:12,770 --> 00:26:15,610
Now the system is fully combined for us.

243
00:26:16,490 --> 00:26:21,310
I didn't change the volts-per-division setting — it's also at 20 volts.

244
00:26:22,270 --> 00:26:26,990
And you can compare with the amplitude that was simply at LC resonance.

245
00:26:28,270 --> 00:26:32,390
How to check that the coil actually stood at quarter wave.

246
00:26:32,810 --> 00:26:36,730
Near the hot end we should have maximum amplitude.

247
00:26:36,730 --> 00:26:43,070
Moving the oscilloscope probe to the cold end, amplitude will be zero.

248
00:26:44,130 --> 00:26:45,710
Now let's try this.

249
00:26:46,890 --> 00:26:57,730
I observed the influence of my hand slightly, so I compensated the frequency a bit by a couple kHz.

250
00:26:58,470 --> 00:27:00,630
And we'll pass through.

251
00:27:02,710 --> 00:27:08,930
Observe the required amplitude and go along the coil.

252
00:27:09,430 --> 00:27:18,370
Lead along it at the same distance and see that moving to the cold end, the amplitude went to zero for us.

253
00:27:19,260 --> 00:27:28,730
On the contrary, when moving to the hot end, amplitude will be at maximum.

254
00:27:30,130 --> 00:27:33,130
Such a simple check.

255
00:27:34,350 --> 00:27:48,350
Now we move to power tests of this build and show in practice what combination means, how the discharge color will change, what effects will happen on the Tesla coil.

256
00:27:48,370 --> 00:27:58,870
So, the experiment will happen for us in such a way that I'll start the system with the help of a half-bridge inverter.

257
00:28:00,690 --> 00:28:08,770
And we'll launch it in the first case without interruption, in the second case I'll turn on interruption from the lab signal generator.

258
00:28:08,770 --> 00:28:18,670
The launch will be from my lab power supply, which you could see earlier in fragments of making this video.

259
00:28:19,270 --> 00:28:23,370
Everything is powered exclusively from a battery.

260
00:28:23,950 --> 00:28:31,070
And generally all experiments of this kind that we'll conduct should be untied from the wall socket.

261
00:28:31,070 --> 00:28:41,280
That is, even when I apply the signal from the lab signal generator here, it's untied at me with the help of an optical driver — opto-isolation happens.

262
00:28:42,510 --> 00:28:47,190
The oscilloscope isn't connected, the probe will lie nearby in the same place the whole time.

263
00:28:47,790 --> 00:28:55,990
The scheme power is done through a DC-DC converter, the scheme of which I gave earlier, with galvanic isolation.

264
00:28:56,090 --> 00:29:00,690
That is, at me there's no single common point with the lighting network.

265
00:29:01,070 --> 00:29:09,070
The experiment is conducted in continuous mode, frequency at the converter output is 330 kHz.

266
00:29:09,450 --> 00:29:22,270
The system isn't tuned now, you see a sine wave, you see the usual phenomenon, the neon lamp burns and we observe the discharge color and length.

267
00:29:24,090 --> 00:29:36,650
Look, here is the discharge — it has a reddish-purple color, the camera slightly distorts the image of course.

268
00:29:36,970 --> 00:29:57,510
And look at the isolated capacity — here you can hear a characteristic click at discharge start, because the capacity is a collector for charged particles.

269
00:29:58,790 --> 00:30:01,230
Remember the discharge color and its length.

270
00:30:02,710 --> 00:30:06,110
So, that's the amplitude we have now.

271
00:30:07,330 --> 00:30:12,470
I introduced the ferrite rod and now we'll observe the discharge.

272
00:30:12,470 --> 00:30:19,110
Now in continuous mode, LC resonance is brought together with the wave on wire length.

273
00:30:19,870 --> 00:30:30,830
See, an interesting crackling appeared at breakdown for us, but the discharge color also remained reddish.

274
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:33,510
The length increased.

275
00:30:35,690 --> 00:30:42,410
Now look at the sphere.

276
00:30:43,830 --> 00:30:48,250
You see an interesting phenomenon appears in the discharge.

277
00:30:48,330 --> 00:30:51,390
Pay attention, the camera will adjust now.

278
00:30:52,650 --> 00:30:56,930
White color appears and a static form of discharge.

279
00:31:00,930 --> 00:31:09,810
That is, the combination of the wave from LC resonance and the wave on wire length generates a new phenomenon in the Tesla coil.

280
00:31:11,130 --> 00:31:13,550
It starts to statically break through.

281
00:31:15,210 --> 00:31:18,730
That is, the Tesla coil starts to suck in the discharge.

282
00:31:19,630 --> 00:31:25,910
Now let's strengthen this phenomenon with control system modulation.

283
00:31:26,910 --> 00:31:37,810
Now I apply from the lab signal generator a pulse with frequency 1 kHz and duration of this pulse is 10%.

284
00:31:38,950 --> 00:31:47,410
We observe what we have on the oscillogram and see the system swings in approximately the usual mode.

285
00:31:47,410 --> 00:31:49,830
But what's interesting.

286
00:31:50,790 --> 00:31:52,830
Now I pulled out the ferrite rod.

287
00:31:53,050 --> 00:31:56,750
Observe the discharge length and its intensity.

288
00:31:58,530 --> 00:32:01,210
See that a sound appeared for us.

289
00:32:02,710 --> 00:32:05,070
The discharge is reddish.

290
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:15,560
On the sphere it becomes with a whitish shade with the presence of statics.

291
00:32:19,580 --> 00:32:23,640
Now I'll introduce the ferrite rod.

292
00:32:24,440 --> 00:32:25,620
Pay attention.

293
00:32:26,340 --> 00:32:27,580
A sweep.

294
00:32:30,500 --> 00:32:37,960
Here now we have LC not combined with the wave on wire length.

295
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:43,340
And we see it wants to converge — wave processes went.

296
00:32:43,340 --> 00:32:48,980
That is, waves with phase difference give us low-frequency oscillations.

297
00:32:51,020 --> 00:32:58,260
And now observe what'll be on the oscillogram when I introduce the ferrite core.

298
00:33:00,700 --> 00:33:02,100
I introduce the core.

299
00:33:07,180 --> 00:33:08,540
See the growth.

300
00:33:09,940 --> 00:33:12,480
And here we reached some level.

301
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:14,340
First moment.

302
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:17,200
Now I'll fix it in this position.

303
00:33:21,760 --> 00:33:22,340
Here it is.

304
00:33:25,690 --> 00:33:28,930
Such an oscillogram with us now.

305
00:33:29,990 --> 00:33:32,710
This is the moment before combination.

306
00:33:33,250 --> 00:33:38,110
That is, full combination hasn't yet happened.

307
00:33:39,110 --> 00:33:40,570
Watch the discharge.

308
00:33:41,590 --> 00:33:44,890
See how its length increased.

309
00:33:45,190 --> 00:33:48,770
Reminder that I don't change power in this parameter.

310
00:33:49,710 --> 00:33:50,910
Intensity.

311
00:33:55,160 --> 00:34:00,320
But the discharge color also has a reddish shade.

312
00:34:04,770 --> 00:34:09,330
And now I'll do full combination.

313
00:34:10,330 --> 00:34:13,490
Watch the oscillogram carefully.

314
00:34:23,810 --> 00:34:25,410
Here's what happens.

315
00:34:30,860 --> 00:34:33,500
Such a picture we have now.

316
00:34:37,660 --> 00:34:39,260
Such fish.

317
00:34:41,060 --> 00:34:43,560
Now look at the phenomenon.

318
00:34:44,260 --> 00:34:46,680
I introduced the ferrite core further.

319
00:34:54,710 --> 00:34:57,650
Look what length comes out.

320
00:35:02,130 --> 00:35:03,170
Here.

321
00:35:04,310 --> 00:35:06,450
The color remained reddish.

322
00:35:07,310 --> 00:35:11,950
And now we need to reduce the duration.

323
00:35:12,190 --> 00:35:14,370
Reminder, now 10%.

324
00:35:15,130 --> 00:35:24,390
Now I'll reduce the duration and show you this same combination effect at 1% duration.

325
00:35:25,260 --> 00:35:30,970
So, duration 1%, frequency also at us 1 kHz modulation.

326
00:35:32,010 --> 00:35:34,650
Accurate combination is absent now.

327
00:35:38,530 --> 00:35:44,910
We have such a picture, quite standard, as we often see.

328
00:35:46,530 --> 00:35:49,410
See the long damping tail.

329
00:35:51,030 --> 00:35:52,070
Here it is.

330
00:35:54,670 --> 00:35:56,810
Look at the discharge now.

331
00:35:57,110 --> 00:36:01,910
That is, we reduced the duration to 1%, voltage remained the same.

332
00:36:03,090 --> 00:36:06,370
And now we spend much less energy.

333
00:36:06,570 --> 00:36:08,010
Observe the discharge.

334
00:36:11,210 --> 00:36:14,350
Look what color it acquires.

335
00:36:14,730 --> 00:36:17,950
It whitens, becomes static.

336
00:36:19,530 --> 00:36:21,830
But this isn't yet full combination.

337
00:36:22,830 --> 00:36:25,270
Amplitude now isn't at maximum.

338
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:32,840
It's clearly visible the discharge has a white color.

339
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:46,090
And now I'll introduce the ferrite rod into the coil.

340
00:36:47,090 --> 00:36:48,730
Observe the oscillogram.

341
00:36:55,620 --> 00:36:57,780
Here's what beauty comes out.

342
00:36:59,520 --> 00:37:02,160
Look if the camera catches.

343
00:37:12,240 --> 00:37:16,960
And sound appears — the coil starts breaking through.

344
00:37:18,820 --> 00:37:25,120
Here is the maximum point of wave convergence of maximum system efficiency.

345
00:37:25,980 --> 00:37:29,140
At that, observe the amplitude — how it grows.

346
00:37:33,230 --> 00:37:34,870
Goes off screen.

347
00:37:38,640 --> 00:37:42,720
And now look what discharge appeared for us.

348
00:37:46,210 --> 00:37:54,210
Audible that the Tesla coil started clicking — breakdowns are already going in air.

349
00:37:57,860 --> 00:38:01,840
See, the discharge length increased.

350
00:38:02,980 --> 00:38:04,500
Observe the color.

351
00:38:08,400 --> 00:38:12,650
And now I'm specifically starting to get hit by current.

352
00:38:16,310 --> 00:38:18,320
Even very strongly.

353
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:21,800
The discharge became powerful, current.

354
00:38:22,060 --> 00:38:24,200
Current component is present.

355
00:38:32,220 --> 00:38:34,140
And the color became bright white.

356
00:38:43,060 --> 00:38:46,650
Such a phenomenon happens for us.

357
00:38:47,640 --> 00:38:49,060
What do we see here?

358
00:38:52,860 --> 00:38:56,840
Now I pulled out the ferrite core and introduce it.

359
00:38:57,520 --> 00:38:58,420
What happens?

360
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:08,780
The wave from LC resonance is an intermediary for transferring energy to the wave on wire length.

361
00:39:10,200 --> 00:39:11,880
In our long line.

362
00:39:12,540 --> 00:39:22,780
And here when maximum interaction in phase happens, you see the ringing now at the end from LC resonance fully disappears.

363
00:39:23,980 --> 00:39:30,060
And we're left with only our maximum amplitude, when two waves exchange energy.

364
00:39:32,340 --> 00:39:46,340
Effectively in the Tesla coil a funnel forms now, which we accelerate with short pulses at its resonance frequency, combined.

365
00:39:47,120 --> 00:39:52,860
And further it starts drawing in physical charges.

366
00:39:57,880 --> 00:39:59,440
Very well audible.

367
00:39:59,580 --> 00:40:02,160
Here already at this distance it starts breaking through.

368
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:08,820
Add voltage now, observe.

369
00:40:12,500 --> 00:40:15,860
Intensity should increase still more.

370
00:40:16,240 --> 00:40:19,480
Here already at this distance the primary breakdown happens.

371
00:40:26,740 --> 00:40:28,480
Well, and from the sphere naturally further.

372
00:40:46,950 --> 00:40:50,690
I'll try to film the effect in darkness still.

373
00:40:51,850 --> 00:40:54,730
Bring the neon bulb to the rod.

374
00:41:02,050 --> 00:41:04,170
Observe what the discharge has become.

375
00:41:05,170 --> 00:41:07,250
Pure static breakdown.

376
00:41:08,210 --> 00:41:08,570
White.

377
00:41:28,900 --> 00:41:30,100
Now on the sphere.

378
00:42:09,040 --> 00:42:12,380
Now a couple of words about making this coil.

379
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:23,120
After winding I soaked the coil with brand-name varnish Shellac from Technohim.

380
00:42:23,680 --> 00:42:29,440
I applied 6 layers here, including soaking the cardboard frame from inside.

381
00:42:30,280 --> 00:42:35,260
It remains to apply several layers of PF231 varnish here.

382
00:42:36,020 --> 00:42:43,040
It's recommended — it doesn't destroy the varnish film from Shellac.

383
00:42:44,060 --> 00:42:52,480
Well, and also, all the most interesting phenomena in the Tesla transformer will be in interruption mode, modulations of amplitude power.

384
00:42:53,520 --> 00:42:56,040
There'll be a further video on my channel about this.

385
00:42:56,040 --> 00:43:02,620
Now I want to say that the inductor here isn't matched with the secondary coil.

386
00:43:02,800 --> 00:43:07,340
That is, I took the first one available so I could just show you these experiments.

387
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:16,520
The inductor also needs to be introduced into resonance, picking its length as a multiple of the turn length of the high-voltage coil — but about that later.

388
00:43:17,160 --> 00:43:21,140
On this I say goodbye, I hope it was interesting and informative for you.

389
00:43:21,140 --> 00:43:26,620
Best of luck to everyone, good experiments, strong health in the new year.
